1. Clone the RISC-V OpenOCD Repository

git clone git@github.com:riscv-collab/riscv-openocd.git <Repo Name>


2. Change Directory to the Repository

cd <Repo Name>


3. Checkout the Specific Commit that is compatible with the patch

git checkout 528970c47ae2157bd7077a5fda04881a024f8d8f


4. Apply the CHERI Changes Patch

patch -p1 -R < PATH_TO_PATCH/cheri_changes.patch

Example: patch -p1 -R < ../cheri_changes.patch

Note: Run this command in the repository's top directory.


5. Verify Successful Patching


6. Build and Install OpenOCD

Refer to the build instructions on the GitHub page:
[https://github.com/riscv-collab/riscv-openocd](https://github.com/riscv-collab/riscv-openocd)
